the%20units%20will%20have%20the%20flexibility%20to%20use%20these%20funds%20to%20acquire%20the%20drones%20that%20are%20the%20most%20effective%20for%20carrying%20out%20mission%20requirements%20at%20the%20front%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3BThis%20marks%20another%20step%20towards%20building%20a%20highly%20flexible%20system%20to%20ensure%20the%20military%20has%20everything%20necessary%20for%20Ukraine's%20defense.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%2C%20Umerov%20announced%20that%20commanders%20would%20now%20be%20able%20to%20purchase%20drones%20%26quot%3Bwithout%20unnecessary%20bureaucratic%20approvals%20from%20the%20General%20Staff%20and%20other%20military%20authorities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine's%20Defense%20Procurement%20Agency%20(DPA)%20has%20been%20leading%20Kyiv's%20centralized%20drone%20procurement%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20the%20agency%20said%20it%20had%20so%20far%20spent%2030%20billion%20UAH%20(around%20%24717%20million)%20acquiring%20drones%20in%202024.%20It%20had%20signed%20contracts%20for%20more%20than%20350%2C000%20drones%20so%20far%20in%20the%20year%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDmytro%20Klimenkov%2C%20Ukraine's%20deputy%20defense%20minister%2C%20said%20at%20the%20time%20that%20such%20efforts%20were%20%26quot%3Baligned%20with%20the%20strategic%20objective%20of%20the%20President%20of%20Ukraine%20to%20supply%20our%20military%20with%20UAVs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%2095%25%20of%20the%20drones%20they%20had%20purchased%20were%20made%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20which%20he%20said%20showed%20%26quot%3Bnotable%20progress%20in%20enhancing%20national%20defense%20technologies%20and%20validates%20the%20high%20quality%20of%20domestic%20products.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225673%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Ukrainian%20multi-purpose%20naval%20drone%20called%20%26quot%3BMagura%20V5%26quot%3B%20during%20a%20demonstration%20in%20April.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F669540829caa6ed01e019d30%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223782%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20multi-purpose%20naval%20drone%20called%20%26quot%3BMagura%20V5.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20Pavlo%20Bahmut%2FUkrinform%2FFuture%20Publishing%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20has%20acted%20as%20a%20kind%20of%20incubator%20for%20drone%20innovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUncrewed%20systems%20have%20dominated%20the%20battlefield%2C%20wreaking%20havoc%20in%20the%20air%2C%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20and%20at%20sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20conflict%20has%20seen%20drones%20deployed%20against%20warships%20and%20tanks%2C%20used%20for%20reconnaissance%2C%20and%20as%20support%20for%20medical%20evacuations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rising%20demand%20for%20such%20technologies%20has%20led%20Kyiv%20to%20issue%20increasingly%20ambitious%20production%20goals.%20Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20said%20earlier%20this%20month%20that%20Ukraine%20wanted%20to%20produce%20%26quot%3Ba%20record%20number%20of%20drones%26quot%3B%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%20December%2C%20the%20Ukrainian%20defense%20ministry%20said%20it%20had%20supplied%20more%20than%201.2%20million%20uncrewed%20aerial%20vehicles%20to%20the%20country's%20armed%20forces%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZelenskyy%20said%20in%20October%20that%20Ukraine%20was%20capable%20of%20manufacturing%20up%20to%204%20million%20drones%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-russia-drones-procurement-war-uav-conflict-kyiv-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737805358000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679267d9ae09223df2bb37ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-russia-drones-procurement-war-uav-conflict-kyiv-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22D